[Seal My Lips with a Kiss]

46
00:02:55,310 --> 00:02:58,277
[Episode 5]

47
00:02:58,277 --> 00:03:00,323
Sorry I suddenly called you over.

48
00:03:00,323 --> 00:03:02,311
Were you surprised?

49
00:03:02,311 --> 00:03:05,244
Of course, I was.

50
00:03:05,244 --> 00:03:08,844
You must also be surprised that I am renting a house with Shioya.

51
00:03:12,211 --> 00:03:15,611
Oh, yes! That too!

52
00:03:16,211 --> 00:03:18,844
Sorry about this.

53
00:03:18,844 --> 00:03:20,547
No problem.

54
00:03:20,547 --> 00:03:24,411
So what did you want to talk about?

55
00:03:24,411 --> 00:03:27,119
Actually, it's a bit complicated.

56
00:03:27,844 --> 00:03:31,983
So I wanted Shioya to be a neutral third party.

57
00:03:33,877 --> 00:03:37,377
What do you mean by "complicated?"

58
00:03:37,377 --> 00:03:42,755
The transition data for Morga Games had omissions.

59
00:03:42,755 --> 00:03:44,344
What?

60
00:03:44,344 --> 00:03:46,344
You must have had a hard time.

61
00:03:46,344 --> 00:03:48,877
The vital data was all missing.

62
00:03:50,544 --> 00:03:53,377
[Sales Department Manual]
[01 Online Ads]

63
00:03:53,377 --> 00:03:55,877
As expected,
[06 Revenue_Out of Event]

64
00:03:55,877 --> 00:03:57,811
there's none.

65
00:03:59,544 --> 00:04:04,515
Is any other transition data missing?

66
00:04:04,515 --> 00:04:09,777
Yes, there was missing data,

67
00:04:09,777 --> 00:04:13,577
and I wasn't allowed to ask certain questions.

68
00:04:13,577 --> 00:04:16,911
But I thought it might be because Usuda-san is too busy.

69
00:04:18,311 --> 00:04:20,911
I hope that's the case, too.

70
00:04:20,911 --> 00:04:22,644
But…

71
00:04:27,377 --> 00:04:30,535
During the transition, could Usuda-san

72
00:04:30,535 --> 00:04:33,987
be deliberately causing you trouble?

73
00:04:35,544 --> 00:04:37,677
"Causing trouble"?

74
00:04:37,677 --> 00:04:42,311
Sato-san, you were also forced to work overtime due to this.

75
00:04:42,311 --> 00:04:47,011
Whether mentally or physically,

76
00:04:47,844 --> 00:04:50,044
you were harmed.

77
00:04:52,877 --> 00:04:56,335
This incident should be reported to the company.

78
00:04:56,811 --> 00:04:59,991
If she is deliberately obstructing your work,

79
00:04:59,991 --> 00:05:03,411
it is also a problem for our entire Sales Dept.

80
00:05:05,515 --> 00:05:08,295
But... to report to the company,

81
00:05:08,295 --> 00:05:11,271
we will need your testimony.

82
00:05:12,077 --> 00:05:14,515
Can you help?

83
00:05:19,944 --> 00:05:22,687
I…

84
00:05:32,144 --> 00:05:33,944
Sato-san.

85
00:05:37,444 --> 00:05:41,423
Don't be nervous. You can take your time.

86
00:05:55,744 --> 00:05:58,671
Before reporting to the company,

87
00:05:59,677 --> 00:06:03,044
may I first speak with Usuda-san?

88
00:06:03,544 --> 00:06:04,977
What?

89
00:06:04,977 --> 00:06:10,577
I think Usuda-san is passionate about work.

90
00:06:11,344 --> 00:06:14,279
I agree.

91
00:06:14,279 --> 00:06:17,144
In fact, I've received a lot of help from her.

92
00:06:17,144 --> 00:06:21,803
If she is deliberately causing trouble at work,

93
00:06:22,544 --> 00:06:25,131
I think she must have a reason.

94
00:06:28,510 --> 00:06:32,244
If we just solve it through the company,

95
00:06:32,844 --> 00:06:36,955
we won't know Usuda-san's reasons.

96
00:06:36,955 --> 00:06:42,144
I feel that wouldn't truly solve the problem.

97
00:06:43,377 --> 00:06:45,177
Therefore,

98
00:06:50,010 --> 00:06:56,275
I think I should have a proper talk with Usuda-san.

99
00:07:01,610 --> 00:07:04,777
Why are you so cool?

100
00:07:06,955 --> 00:07:08,711
I see.

101
00:07:08,711 --> 00:07:11,739
I'll arrange a place for your talk.

102
00:07:13,710 --> 00:07:15,977
Thank you.

103
00:07:16,710 --> 00:07:20,977
One thing really concerns me.

104
00:07:22,544 --> 00:07:27,944
You didn't have much interaction with Usuda-san before, right?

105
00:07:27,944 --> 00:07:30,110
That's right.

106
00:07:30,810 --> 00:07:35,911
But it seems she hasn't liked you for a while.

107
00:07:37,277 --> 00:07:41,207
Can you think of any reason for that?

108
00:07:42,144 --> 00:07:45,807
"Reason"…

109
00:07:47,410 --> 00:07:51,344
Usuda and I are friends.

110
00:07:56,677 --> 00:07:58,044
Sato?

111
00:07:58,044 --> 00:08:01,577
Sato-san, are you all right?

112
00:08:01,577 --> 00:08:04,687
I'm fine.

113
00:08:05,610 --> 00:08:07,910
Did you think of anything?

114
00:08:08,544 --> 00:08:14,035
No, maybe it was my misunderstanding.

115
00:08:18,377 --> 00:08:20,377
Shibayama?

116
00:08:21,110 --> 00:08:23,577
Sorry, I need to take this call.

117
00:08:25,510 --> 00:08:27,235
Yes.

118
00:08:34,844 --> 00:08:37,177
Don't take it all on yourself.

119
00:08:37,844 --> 00:08:41,410
If there's anything, just say it.

120
00:08:43,144 --> 00:08:45,210
Thank you.

121
00:08:45,844 --> 00:08:48,910
I understand. I'll go over right away.

122
00:08:51,910 --> 00:08:53,744
It seems Shibayama made a mistake.

123
00:08:53,744 --> 00:08:55,610
I'll be right back.

124
00:08:56,177 --> 00:08:57,977
Are you going there now?

125
00:08:57,977 --> 00:08:59,210
Yes.

126
00:08:59,210 --> 00:09:02,744
Sato, I'll take you to the station on the way.

127
00:09:05,510 --> 00:09:07,644
But you haven't had dinner yet, have you?

128
00:09:07,644 --> 00:09:09,944
Shioya, Sato's dinner is your treat.

129
00:09:09,944 --> 00:09:11,683
Take her somewhere nice to eat.

130
00:09:11,683 --> 00:09:13,477
I will.

131
00:09:14,310 --> 00:09:18,915
Mizoguchi-san, thank you so much.

132
00:09:18,915 --> 00:09:24,444
If there's any way I can help, you can always tell me.

133
00:09:25,244 --> 00:09:27,710
Okay, thanks.

134
00:09:27,710 --> 00:09:33,277
Wait, that's not good for my hair roots.

135
00:09:33,277 --> 00:09:35,044
Don't think of pushing me away.

136
00:09:35,044 --> 00:09:36,519
Socially,

137
00:09:36,519 --> 00:09:38,177
it's not very appropriate either.

138
00:09:38,177 --> 00:09:41,810
Seriously, you just talk of social norms.

139
00:09:41,810 --> 00:09:43,610
No, I don't.

140
00:09:43,610 --> 00:09:45,410
All right, all right.

141
00:09:45,410 --> 00:09:48,210
Shioya, I'll leave it to you then.

142
00:10:16,777 --> 00:10:19,344
Wait, wait… That's too much force.

143
00:10:19,344 --> 00:10:21,543
Hair… my hair.

144
00:10:21,543 --> 00:10:25,477
I'll go bald. I'll go bald!

145
00:10:29,211 --> 00:10:30,980
This is disinfecting.

146
00:10:32,111 --> 00:10:35,111
"Disinfecting"?

147
00:10:40,544 --> 00:10:45,167
Where Mizoguchi touched you must be disinfected.

148
00:10:59,377 --> 00:11:01,077
Here too.

149
00:11:15,611 --> 00:11:20,044
Wait… wait a moment.

150
00:11:20,877 --> 00:11:23,811
If Mizoguchi-san comes back…

151
00:11:55,511 --> 00:12:01,027
He didn't touch me there.

152
00:12:37,911 --> 00:12:42,277
Sato-san, you're my woman.

153
00:12:43,211 --> 00:12:44,844
What?

154
00:13:00,944 --> 00:13:06,211
I'll definitely protect you, Sato-san.

155
00:13:20,211 --> 00:13:23,020
I think I should

156
00:13:23,020 --> 00:13:26,510
have a proper talk with Usuda-san.

157
00:13:34,611 --> 00:13:36,877
What was I doing?

158
00:13:38,877 --> 00:13:40,477
Shibayama, are you all right?

159
00:13:40,477 --> 00:13:43,211
Mizoguchi-san, thank you for coming to help.

160
00:13:43,211 --> 00:13:44,939
You said there was a mistake in the contract.

161
00:13:44,939 --> 00:13:48,675
I found a mistake in the amount during the final check.

162
00:13:50,577 --> 00:13:53,099
Is the amount wrong?
[Contract ¥12 million ($83,000) with assurance]

163
00:13:53,099 --> 00:13:55,527
What is the correct amount?

164
00:13:57,677 --> 00:13:58,877
Here.
[Contract ¥15 million ($104,000) with assurance]

165
00:13:58,877 --> 00:14:01,020
I don't know why the amount was altered.

166
00:14:01,020 --> 00:14:02,970
[Changed to ¥12 million without assurance]

167
00:14:06,911 --> 00:14:08,944
This handwriting…

168
00:14:10,211 --> 00:14:12,444
Is something wrong?

169
00:14:12,444 --> 00:14:13,644
No.

170
00:14:13,644 --> 00:14:15,499
Let's quickly adjust and submit it tomorrow.

171
00:14:15,499 --> 00:14:16,911
We can make it, right?

172
00:14:16,911 --> 00:14:18,911
I'll go with you to apologize to the section chief.

173
00:14:18,911 --> 00:14:22,611
Really? Mizoguchi-san, you are so nice.

174
00:14:22,611 --> 00:14:24,623
Thank you!

175
00:14:30,077 --> 00:14:31,871
Look at this.

176
00:14:33,844 --> 00:14:35,977
This is…

177
00:14:36,577 --> 00:14:41,151
Shibayama-kun's case I handled a while ago, right?

178
00:14:42,244 --> 00:14:44,111
It's strange.

179
00:14:44,111 --> 00:14:50,577
The content is different from when I handled it.

180
00:14:52,277 --> 00:14:54,277
So it is true.

181
00:14:55,187 --> 00:14:56,707
What?

182
00:14:56,707 --> 00:15:00,644
Usuda-san must have changed it, right?

183
00:15:01,811 --> 00:15:03,944
How is that possible?

184
00:15:05,677 --> 00:15:07,744
This is Usuda-san's handwriting.

185
00:15:07,744 --> 00:15:09,644
I'm certain.

186
00:15:15,771 --> 00:15:18,511
[Changed to ¥12 million without assurance]

187
00:15:20,739 --> 00:15:24,395
[Person in charge changed from Yokogawa-san to Yamamoto-san]

188
00:15:24,395 --> 00:15:26,577
[Changed to ¥12 million without assurance]

189
00:15:28,911 --> 00:15:31,044
Why?

190
00:15:33,477 --> 00:15:36,060
This time, Shibayama noticed beforehand,

191
00:15:36,060 --> 00:15:38,510
to fix the issue with the contract.

192
00:15:38,511 --> 00:15:40,244
However…

193
00:15:40,244 --> 00:15:42,911
If it went unnoticed,

194
00:15:45,277 --> 00:15:48,211
things would have been terrible.

195
00:15:53,311 --> 00:15:55,259
Where are you going?

196
00:15:55,259 --> 00:15:57,386
I want to talk to Usuda-san!

197
00:15:57,386 --> 00:16:01,044
She almost hurt the entire Sales Dept. just to frame me.

198
00:16:01,044 --> 00:16:03,311
I will never forgive her!

199
00:16:04,311 --> 00:16:05,944
Sato!

200
00:16:07,344 --> 00:16:09,511
Sato, wait a moment.

201
00:16:12,477 --> 00:16:15,007
Shioya, quickly stop her!

202
00:16:15,007 --> 00:16:17,477
I'm sorry, I'm in a hurry.

203
00:16:22,477 --> 00:16:24,144
What's going on?

204
00:16:24,144 --> 00:16:26,144
How should I put it?

205
00:16:26,144 --> 00:16:28,244
Please let go of me.

206
00:16:28,244 --> 00:16:30,144
Calm down first.

207
00:16:30,144 --> 00:16:33,011
Didn't I say I would arrange your talk with Usuda-san?

208
00:16:33,011 --> 00:16:36,277
While I wait for that, something like this might happen again!

209
00:16:36,277 --> 00:16:40,577
Then it will impact the company's profit!

210
00:16:40,577 --> 00:16:43,444
I see, I think I understand what happened.

211
00:16:43,444 --> 00:16:45,963
If so, please let go of me!

212
00:16:45,963 --> 00:16:50,777
Don't you want to know Usuda-san's reasons?

213
00:16:51,877 --> 00:16:54,377
If you talk to her directly now,

214
00:16:54,377 --> 00:16:57,444
Usuda-san won't reveal anything.

215
00:16:57,444 --> 00:17:02,695
Still, everyone might be in a worse situation with me.

216
00:17:02,695 --> 00:17:06,844
I must go and settle the matter!

217
00:17:13,011 --> 00:17:17,577
Do you really think that will settle it?

218
00:17:20,911 --> 00:17:25,167
To be blunt, I doubt your current approach

219
00:17:25,167 --> 00:17:29,335
will achieve what you truly want.

220
00:17:29,335 --> 00:17:33,177
Do you really think that would be good?

221
00:17:51,477 --> 00:17:56,177
I… was hasty.

222
00:17:57,144 --> 00:18:00,377
I apologize.

223
00:18:02,244 --> 00:18:04,777
I'm glad you calmed down.

224
00:18:05,644 --> 00:18:07,971
But what should we do about it?

225
00:18:07,971 --> 00:18:09,670
Even if we go to Usuda-san,

226
00:18:09,670 --> 00:18:13,440
will she really tell us the truth?

227
00:18:13,977 --> 00:18:18,155
Then... let's strategize.

228
00:18:23,377 --> 00:18:25,211
Let's arrange it this way.

229
00:18:25,844 --> 00:18:27,377
I understand.

230
00:18:27,377 --> 00:18:30,477
All right, I'll arrange it.

231
00:18:32,077 --> 00:18:34,377
I'll return to work now.

232
00:18:34,377 --> 00:18:38,955
I'm sorry. Thank you very much.

233
00:18:46,744 --> 00:18:50,444
I must also apologize to you, Shioya-san.

234
00:18:51,144 --> 00:18:53,511
Let's go back to work, too.

235
00:19:00,577 --> 00:19:02,711
I'm sorry about earlier.

236
00:19:03,777 --> 00:19:06,144
I was harsh.

237
00:19:09,511 --> 00:19:11,911
I'm the one who should apologize.

238
00:19:12,744 --> 00:19:15,010
If not for your words,

239
00:19:15,010 --> 00:19:17,840
I would have acted rashly.

240
00:19:19,944 --> 00:19:22,977
Thank you for stopping me.

241
00:19:31,044 --> 00:19:33,344
Don't take it all on yourself.

242
00:19:36,744 --> 00:19:41,040
If anything else happens,

243
00:19:42,390 --> 00:19:44,780
you must rely on me.

244
00:19:50,977 --> 00:19:52,575
Okay.

245
00:19:55,211 --> 00:19:57,177
Mizoguchi-kun.

246
00:19:58,411 --> 00:20:00,611
Is he not here yet?

247
00:20:10,411 --> 00:20:12,244
Please come in.

248
00:20:16,611 --> 00:20:18,577
What's going on?

249
00:20:26,444 --> 00:20:30,777
I'm sorry for deceiving you.

250
00:20:31,911 --> 00:20:37,044
But... I have something to say to you.

251
00:20:37,044 --> 00:20:40,044
I had an appointment with Mizoguchi-kun.

252
00:20:40,044 --> 00:20:43,177
I have nothing to say to you.

253
00:20:45,977 --> 00:20:48,344
It's important.

254
00:20:53,210 --> 00:20:55,944
I can't believe you thought of such a thing.

255
00:20:57,044 --> 00:21:00,935
After Usuda-san enters, we will leave you two alone.

256
00:21:00,935 --> 00:21:06,344
Then keep our phone call open.

257
00:21:07,710 --> 00:21:09,644
We will block the door.

258
00:21:09,644 --> 00:21:12,675
If anything happens, we will enter at once.

259
00:21:12,675 --> 00:21:14,477
Don't worry.

260
00:21:14,477 --> 00:21:16,177
Okay.

261
00:21:16,750 --> 00:21:19,077
[Changed to ¥12 million without assurance]

262
00:21:19,077 --> 00:21:24,895
Isn't this your handwriting with the altered incorrect amount?

263
00:21:25,777 --> 00:21:27,844
No, that's not my handwriting.

264
00:21:27,844 --> 00:21:28,844
But…

265
00:21:28,844 --> 00:21:32,777
Are you trying to threaten me with baseless accusations?

266
00:21:37,077 --> 00:21:39,310
There's one more thing:

267
00:21:39,310 --> 00:21:42,777
The Handover Manual excluded important information.

268
00:21:42,777 --> 00:21:46,187
Many projects don't have written records.

269
00:21:46,187 --> 00:21:49,344
Only incompetent workers would shift the blame onto others.

270
00:21:49,344 --> 00:21:51,877
Mizoguchi-san confirmed it for me.

271
00:21:51,877 --> 00:21:56,477
The vital data required was missing from the very start.

272
00:21:57,877 --> 00:21:59,455
Really?

273
00:21:59,455 --> 00:22:05,706
So you instigated Mizoguchi-kun to come to me at that time.

274
00:22:05,706 --> 00:22:07,591
No, I did not.

275
00:22:07,591 --> 00:22:10,077
Mizoguchi-san just confirmed it with me.

276
00:22:10,077 --> 00:22:16,271
Seducing men to frame others is your method, right?

277
00:22:16,271 --> 00:22:17,339
What?

278
00:22:17,339 --> 00:22:21,607
I won't allow a despicable woman like you in the Sales Dept.

279
00:22:21,607 --> 00:22:24,647
If not for you, she wouldn't have…

280
00:22:26,846 --> 00:22:30,877
Are you talking about Oribe-san?

281
00:22:33,515 --> 00:22:37,939
Is this Oribe-san, the one who left two years ago?

282
00:22:37,939 --> 00:22:40,210
Why suddenly mention her?

283
00:22:44,210 --> 00:22:46,910
- About Oribe-san—
- Shut up!

284
00:22:50,010 --> 00:22:51,610
I know it all!

285
00:22:51,610 --> 00:22:55,610
You cornered Oribe and made her resign.

286
00:22:58,042 --> 00:22:59,611
What?

287
00:23:04,977 --> 00:23:06,410
